com.mumfrey.liteloader.transformers.event.json

Class JsonEvents

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mumfrey.liteloader.transformers.event.json.JsonEvents
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ObfProvider, java.io.Serializable

    public class JsonEvents
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, ObfProvider
    Serialisable class which represents a set of event injection definitions. Instances of this class are created by deserialising with JSON. The JSON string should be passed to the static parse() method which returns an instance of the class.

    After parsing, the events defined here can be injected into an event transformer instance by calling the register(com.mumfrey.liteloader.transformers.event.json.ModEventInjectionTransformer) method.

    Author:
    Adam Mummery-Smith
